---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Justin"
	description="Practicing accessible, responsive front-end techniques while indulging in a Frutiger Aero aesthetic."
	pubDate={new Date('March 06 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Welcome to my personal home on the web. This repository is a digital sandbox where I explore 
		modern tooling while capturing the spirit of the mid-2000s web.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>What I'm Experimenting With:</strong>
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Frutiger Aero Aesthetic:</strong> Re-creating the optimism of the mid-2000s (Aero Glass, 
			glossy gradients, and nature-inspired palettes) using modern, lightweight CSS techniques.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Accessibility & Modern Tooling:</strong> Using the power of Astro 5 to build a static-first 
			site that remains keyboard and screen-reader accessible despite its glossy appearance.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Digital Anthropology:</strong> Studying how our biological "caveman brains" navigate 
			the high-speed tension of the digital age.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		I'm focused on creating a "Single-Window" experience that prioritizes readability and 
		long-term sustainability. By using clean Markdown for my posts and modular Astro components for 
		my layout, I can focus on writing and building without being slowed down by library maintenance.
	</p>

	<p>
		<em>Stay optimistic, stay glossy.</em>
	</p>
</Layout>
